Program: Crossing Continents
Title: A Mediterranean Rescue
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b063cxn8
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 3 Aug 2015
In one of the largest operations of its kind, thousands of migrants, mostly from sub-Saharan Africa, were pulled off cramped, unseaworthy boats in the Mediterranean in June. Gabriel Gatehouse has had rare access to the operation. He follows two young men as they try to find a new home in Europe, from the moment they board a privately-funded search and rescue ship, to their attempts to evade the Italian police. Show less